@NODE intro "Introduction"
@{u}Introduction@{uu}

   This little door tells your users how much their call is costing by working
out where they live, asking their phone company then figuring what the cost
band is and finally comming up with the cost (phew).

   It works by holding all the known rates in a directory for each phone
company, it then sees what time it is - peak, cheap or weekend rate, and then
looks in a list of local STD codes and regional STD codes for the phone company
they chose and if it is then it displays the appropriate cost.

P.S. This has been made much easier to use in recent versions.

@{u}Requirements@{uu}

MAX's BBS 1.54 68000 version or MAX's Pro.
A BT Phone Book, or at least a list of your local and regional STD codes.
`LSD_Doors.key', `Halfreg.key' or `Otherreg.key' in `Sys:S/' to get rid of
the skint-sysop message ;).

Thats ya lot :).

@ENDNODE


